loudflare D1)**, and fixes **cross-list aggregation** of inconsistent song sets. Full design in [`docs/import-redesign-spec.md`](docs/import-redesign-spec.md); how-to in [`README.md`](README.md).\n\n## Highlights\n- **Submit page** (`submit.html`): paste/upload → fuzzy match → confirm-and-fix (album art, missing-songs, event picker) → submit; **goes live immediately** (no admin/moderation, no PR).\n- **Matcher** (`src/matcher.ts`): normalize → multi-key resolve with **null-on-collision**, artist-half disambiguation, graded fuzzy candidates, learned aliases. 100% match on the existing `.txt` data.\n- **Event/concert-leg scope**: rank a show's setlist (union of both days); per-leg slugs from the leg name in Japanese (`hasu6th埼玉`); deep-link into the-sorter via `?performanceIds=`.\n- **Fair aggregation** (`src/aggregate.ts`): eligibility-aware normalized rank + shrinkage + Borda — \"not ranked\" ≠ \"ranked last\"; wired into the UI via `/api/aggregate`.\n- Album art throughout; `index.html` rewired to the API.\n\n## ⚠️ Deployment — new infrastructure (read before merging)\nThis changes the project **from a zero-infra static site to a small backend service.** The submit/match/aggregate logic runs in `functions/api/**` against **Cloudflare D1**; GitHub Pages is static-only and can't run it, so the app moves to **Cloudflare Pages + Functions + D1**.\n\n- **Maintainer needs:** a **Cloudflare account** (new signup; free tier is plenty) + `wrangler` CLI authed once. **Local dev needs nothing new** (`bun run local:setup && bun run dev`).\n- **One-time setup + gotchas** (site moves off GitHub Pages; `ALTER TABLE` needed for later schema changes on an existing DB; new concerts don't auto-sync yet) are documented in the **\"Deployment (for the maintainer)\"** section of the README.\n\n## Verified\n`bun run typecheck` clean · `bun run test:matcher` 100% · endpoints + submit→live + per-leg/event aggregation exercised end-to-end.\n\n## Follow-ups (separate PRs)\n- Scheduled catalog